==English==

===Etymology===
Latin.  Originally meant "head of hair".

It has a persian root:
It's made of 2 parts: "kay" means "Mithraist King" and "sar" means "head or top". so it means head of the kings.
This is the title of Roman emperors when they became mithraist.

===Pronunciation===
*Latin [[IPA|IPA]]: /ˈkaisar/
*English (''rhotic'') [[IPA|IPA]]: /ˈsiːzər/
*English (''non-rhotic'') [[IPA|IPA]]: /ˈsiːzə/ 

